verbose_text: However, we cannot rule out that the effect of GDC-0941 and BKM120 on SGK3 activity in these studies is not at least partially mediated through the ability of these inhibitors to suppress the activity of mTORC2, which is potentially also regulated by class I PI3K [XREF_BIBR] (XREF_FIG).
evidence: GDC-0941 and BKM120 on SGK3 activity in these studies is not at least partially mediated through the ability of these inhibitors to suppress the activity of mTORC2
